# A real enumeration exchange, replayable without tshark.
#
# UDP payloads lifted verbatim from reference/intellivue_enumeration.pcapng, in
# capture order. One payload per line, hex; '#' starts a comment.
#
# This is the smallest subset that reproduces the *whole* capture's inventory --
# all 25 signals with identical labels, label codes, display strings and units --
# while still letting collect_enumeration() terminate on its own, because it
# includes the final RORS that closes each of the three polled object classes.
# It was minimised mechanically against the full capture, not chosen by hand.
#
# frame  message type                       carries
# 6      MDSCreateEvent                     MDS attributes (incl. object support)
# 51     LinkedMDSExtendedPollActionResult  10 numerics
# 52     LinkedMDSExtendedPollActionResult  10 numerics
# 53     MDSExtendedPollActionResult        closes NOM_MOC_VMO_METRIC_NU
# 70     MDSExtendedPollActionResult        waves 686, 986
# 74     MDSExtendedPollActionResult        waves 2332, 696
# 78     MDSExtendedPollActionResult        *labels* wave 696 (Resp)
# 130    MDSExtendedPollActionResult        *labels* wave 686 (ECG Lead MCL),
#                                           closes NOM_MOC_VMO_METRIC_SA_RT
# 143    MDSExtendedPollActionResult        1 alarm, closes NOM_MOC_VMO_AL_MON
#
# Frames 78 and 130 are why this file is not just "the first poll cycle": waves
# 686 and 696 are first reported bare, and only a later cycle names them. An
# enumerator that stopped at the first reply would report two unlabelled waves.




e10000020002002a03eb00070024002100000000f13b001a000000000d617300ffffffffffffffff00010006000000000000




